Web Crawling melalui Public API

Crawling Data Ekspor melalui WebAPI BPS

library(tidyverse)

Note: Ganti XXXX dengan API key pribadi

endPoint <- "https://webapi.bps.go.id/v1/api/dataexim"
query <- list(sumber = 1, 
              kodehs = '01',
              jenishs = 1, 
              tahun = 2020, 
              periode = 1, 
              key = 'XXXX')

url <- paste(endPoint, paste0(names(query), "/", unlist(query), collapse = "/"), sep = "/")
url
library(jsonlite)

data <- fromJSON(url)

ChatGPT

openai_key = 'XXXX'
ask_chatgpt <- function(prompt) {

response <- POST(
  url = "https://api.openai.com/v1/chat/completions", 
  add_headers(Authorization = paste("Bearer", openai_key)),
  content_type_json(),
  encode = "json",
  body = list(
    model = "gpt-3.5-turbo",
    messages = list(list(
      role = "user", 
      content = prompt 
      ))
    )
  )

cat(str_trim(content(response)$choices[[1]]$message$content))

}
ask_chatgpt("Bagaimana pendapatmu tentang Statistika IPB?")

HTML Parsing

HTML Parsing dengan Regular Expression (RegEx)

Contoh Regular Expression dalam R

library(stringr)

text <- c("nur@gmail.com", "08128712", "Didi123@email.id", "F4523NM")

str_subset(text, 'a')
## [1] "nur@gmail.com"    "Didi123@email.id"
str_detect(text, '[0-9]')
## [1] FALSE  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE
str_extract(text, '[a-z]+')
## [1] "nur" NA    "idi" NA
str_extract_all(text, '[a-z]+')
## [[1]]
## [1] "nur"   "gmail" "com"  
## 
## [[2]]
## character(0)
## 
## [[3]]
## [1] "idi"   "email" "id"   
## 
## [[4]]
## character(0)
str_replace(text, 'com|id', 'net')
## [1] "nur@gmail.net"     "08128712"          "Dneti123@email.id"
## [4] "F4523NM"
str_replace_all(text, '[^a-z0-9]', '#')
## [1] "nur#gmail#com"    "08128712"         "#idi123#email#id" "#4523##"

Contoh: HTML Parsing dengan Regular Expression (RegEx)

library(stringr)

url <- "https://ngopi.tiiny.site"
pageSource <- paste(readLines(url), collapse = " ")
pageSource %>% 
  str_extract_all('08[\\d -]+') %>% 
  unlist %>% 
  str_remove_all('\\D')
## [1] "081234532421" "08126663242"  "0812345333"
pageSource %>% 
  str_extract_all('<em>.+?<\\/em>') %>% 
  unlist %>% 
  str_remove_all('\\D')     
## [1] "081234532421" "08126663242"  "0812345333"

HTML Parsing dengan HTML Parser: rvest

Select all-element vs Looping

brand <- page %>%   
    html_elements(".mod-b-card__title") %>%
  html_text2()

km <- page %>%   
    html_elements(".mod-b-card__car-other") %>%
  html_element("span") %>%
  html_text2()

price <- page %>%   
    html_elements(".mod-card__price__total") %>%
  html_text2()

Select all-element vs Looping (3)

getdata <- function(card){
  c(
    brand = card %>% 
      html_element(".mod-b-card__title") %>%
      html_text2(),
    km = card %>%
      html_element(".mod-b-card__car-other") %>%
      html_element("span") %>%
      html_text2(),
    price = card %>% 
      html_element(".mod-card__price__total") %>%
      html_text2()
  )
}

page %>% 
  html_elements(".mod-b-card__footer") %>%
  lapply(getdata) %>%
  dplyr::bind_rows()

Ekstraksi Data JSON dari HTML

JSON-LD

library(rvest)
library(jsonlite)

url <- "https://www.lazada.co.id/products/evercoss-m6a-3gb-ram-3gb-rom-16gb-i5680398897-s11127566246.html"
product <- read_html(url) %>% 
  html_node(xpath = '//script[@type ="application/ld+json"]') %>% 
  html_text() %>% 
  fromJSON()

JSON sebagai Value dari Suatu Attribute

library(rvest)
library(jsonlite)

url <- 'https://www.strava.com/activities/7203369384'
activity <- read_html(url) %>% 
  html_element(xpath = '//div[@data-react-class="ActivityPublic"]') %>%
  html_attr('data-react-props') %>%
  fromJSON()

JSON sebagai Internal JavaScript Variable

library(rvest)
library(jsonlite)
library(stringr)

url <- "https://www.matahari.com/bali-lestari-pdml-08-pdml-doby-silky-lengan-panjang-105078212.html"
product <- read_html(url) %>% 
  html_element(xpath = '//*[contains(text(), "window.insider_object.product")]') %>% 
  html_text2() %>%
  str_replace('.*= (\\{.+?\\}).*', '\\1') %>%
  fromJSON()

tryCatch untuk Error Handling

urls <- c("https://stat.ipb.ac.id",  "https://stats.ipb.ac.id", "https://ipb.ac.id")

library(rvest)

getHeader <- function(url){
  message(paste("Try to scrape:", url))
  url %>% read_html %>% html_element('h1') %>% html_text2()
}

lapply(urls, getHeader)
## Try to scrape: https://stat.ipb.ac.id
## Try to scrape: https://stats.ipb.ac.id
## Error in open.connection(x, "rb"): Could not resolve host: stats.ipb.ac.id
getHeader <- function(url) {
  out <- tryCatch(
    {
      message(paste("Try to scrape:", url))
      url %>% read_html %>% html_element('h1') %>% html_text2()
    },
    error=function(e) {
      message(paste("Error encounted for:", url))
      message("Here's the original error message:")
      message(e)
      return(NA)
    },
    warning=function(e) {
      message(paste("URL caused a warning:", url))
      message("Here's the original warning message:")
      message(e)
      return(NULL)
    },
    finally={
      message(paste("Processed URL:", url, "\n"))
    }
  )    
  return(out)
}


lapply(urls, getHeader)
## Try to scrape: https://stat.ipb.ac.id
## Processed URL: https://stat.ipb.ac.id
## Try to scrape: https://stats.ipb.ac.id
## Error encounted for: https://stats.ipb.ac.id
## Here's the original error message:
## Error in open.connection(x, "rb"): Could not resolve host: stats.ipb.ac.id
## Processed URL: https://stats.ipb.ac.id
